er experiences by reducing reliance on disjointed tool stacks. Demand is increasing for API-first, composable architectures that provide seamless integ...\n\n---\n\n## Current Phase - Other Fields Already Filled\n\n- **V0 Lovable Prompts**: {"v0_prompt":"It appears there was an error when trying to create the V0 project using the prompt. However, you can copy the following detailed prompt and try to submit it directly into the V0 API yourself, following the correct format outlined in the V0 documentation.\\n\\nHereâ€™s the comprehensive V0 design prompt for generating the UI prototypes for your product:\\n\\n```markdown\\n## UI Design Prompt for Comprehensive User Experience Platform\\n\\n**Description**: Create a cohesive and intuitive platform for tech-savvy professionals and organizations to streamline their workflows, reduce user fragmentation, and enhance operational efficiency. The platform will include essential functionalities consolidated into a user-friendly interface designed for SMEs and larger corporations.\\n\\n### UI Components Needed:\\n1. **Landing Page**\\n    - Hero section with a brief value proposition and primary call-to-action button (CTA).\\n    - Features section highlighting key functionalities with icons and short descriptions.\\n    - Testimonials slider for user feedback and satisfaction insights.\\n    - Footer with quick links and contact information.\\n\\n2. **Onboarding Flow**\\n    - **Sign Up/Login Form**: Input fields for email, password, and submit button. Include 'Forgot Password?' link.\\n    - **Guided Tutorial Modal**: Step-by-step walkthrough overlay with navigation buttons (Next, Prev, Exit).\\n    - **Personalization Settings**: A form for users to customize dashboards (dropdowns for themes, toggle switches for notifications).\\n\\n3. **Dashboard**\\n    - **Main Navigation Bar**: Horizontal layout with icons for Home, Tasks, Collaboration, and Settings. Use responsive design for collapsing into a hamburger menu on mobile.\\n4. **Task Management Interface**\\n    - **Task List**: A table layout with sortable columns (Task Name, Due Date, Status). Include an Add Task button.\\n    - **Task Detail View**: Modal window displaying full task details, comments section, and a button for marking as complete.\\n\\n5. **Collaboration Tools**\\n    - **Chat Interface**: Side panel with user list, chat history, and input box for sending messages.\\n    - **Document Sharing Area**: Drag-and-drop upload feature and document preview options.\\n\\n### Layout and Structure:\\n- Use a mobile-first approach for responsive design.\\n- Flexbox layout for the dashboard to adjust cards based on screen size.\\n### Styling Preferences:\\n- **Color Scheme**: Primary color #1F2937 (Slate Gray), Secondary color #3B82F6 (Sky Blue) for CTAs, Accent colors for success and error messages (Green for success messages, Red for errors).\\n- **Typography**: Use a modern sans-serif font such as *Inter* or *Roboto*. Headings should be bold and larger (24px), body text should be regular weight (16px).\\n- Maintain consistent button styles with rounded corners and shadow effects.\\n\\n### Accessibility Considerations:\\n- All interactive elements must have clear ARIA labels for assistive technologies.\\n- Ensure sufficient color contrast between text and background to meet Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) AA standards.\\n- Include keyboard navigation support (Tab index for interactive elements).\\n- Utilize focus states for all buttons and links.\\n\\n### Modern Design Patterns:\\n- Implement a **card-based design** for displaying multiple functionalities on the dashboard.\\n- Use **modular forms** for onboarding, with progressive disclosure to minimize cognitive load.\\n- Incorporate feedback mechanisms that provide instant responses to user actions (e.g., confirmation messages, loading spinners).\\n\\n### User Flows Integration:\\n- Reflect the defined key user flowsâ€”Onboarding, Task Completion, Collaboration, and Feedback Assessmentâ€”across UI components for seamless transitions and interactions.\\n\\nThis detailed prompt is structured to guide the design process, ensuring a tailored solution addressing the identified user experience challenges while adhering to best practices in modern UI design.\\n```\\n\\nYou can now try to input this prompt into the V0 API. If you encounter any further issues, please let me know!","lovable_prompt":""}\n\n---\n\n## Current Form Data (All Fields)\n\nThe following information has already been provided in this form:\n\n- **V0 Lovable Prompts**: {"v0_prompt":"It appears there was an error when trying to create the V0 project using the prompt. However, you can copy the following detailed prompt and try to submit it directly into the V0 API yourself, following the correct format outlined in the V0 documentation.\\n\\nHereâ€™s the comprehensive V0 design prompt for generating the UI prototypes for your product:\\n\\n```markdown\\n## UI Design Prompt for Comprehensive User Experience Platform\\n\\n**Description**: Create a cohesive and intuitive pla...\n\nUse this information to ensure consistency and build upon what has already been provided.\n\n---\n\n## Industry Standards & Best Practices\n\nPlease ensure the response follows industry standards from:\n- BCS (British Computer Society) Product Management Framework\n- ICAgile (International Consortium for Agile) Product Ownership\n- AIPMM (Association of International Product Marketing and Management)\n- Pragmatic Institute Product Management Framework\n- McKinsey CodeBeyond standards\n\nThe response should be:\n- Professional and industry-standard compliant\n- Well-structured and comprehensive\n- Actionable and measurable\n- Aligned with best practices\n\n---\n\nI'm working on the "Design" phase of my product lifecycle.\n\nBased on all the context provided above (previous conversations, previous phases, all form data, and knowledge base),\nplease help me generate a concise response for the following question:\n\n**Question**: Describe the user experience and key user flows\n\n**Field**: User Experience\n\nPlease provide a concise, focused response (2-3 paragraphs maximum). Be direct and to the point while maintaining quality and relevance.\n\nPlease generate a well-structured response that:\n- Takes into account ALL previous information, conversations, and form data\n- Leverages knowledge from the RAG knowledge base\n- Is specific and relevant to the product being developed\n- Provides actionable and comprehensive information\n- Maintains consistency with previously provided information\n- Follows industry standards and best practices\n- Is professional and well-formatted\n\nGenerate only the content for this specific field, without repeating the question or adding extra formatting.	\N	\N	{}	2025-11-30 01:05:24.542659+00	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
5ab7352c-c8dd-4c16-b35f-94ea92517a2e	8743ff89-b38a-4db3-b7fe-9dc40607a7e4	\N	\N	agent	strategy	strategy	The user experience (UX) of the product is crafted to unify onboarding, task management, collaboration, and feedback into a seamless interface tailored for tech-savvy professionals in mid-market and enterprise organizations. This persona-driven approach aims to eliminate user frustration caused by fragmented solutions. Users begin their journey on a mobile-first, card-based dashboard featuring prioritized tasks and collaboration threads, with quick actions available. Visual consistency and trust are maintained using the V0 design standards such as Slate Gray and Sky Blue color schemes, Inter/Roboto typography, while ensuring accessibility via WCAG AA compliance, ARIA labels, and keyboard navigation.\n\nKey user flows are designed to be intuitive and efficient: \n1. **Onboarding** involves a streamlined sign-up/login process, guided tutorials, and personalization settings that quickly configure the user's dashboard and notifications, ensuring a swift time-to-first-value.\n2. **Core Task Workflow** enables users to create, assign, and sort tasks easily, with a detailed task-view modal for comments, and attachments, culminating in a simple task completion process.\n3. **Collaboration & Sharing** tools include a side-panel chat and document sharing feature with drag-and-drop functionality, ensuring document previews and contextual task linking are all effortlessly integrated.\n4. **Feedback & Iteration** capture essential metrics such as task completion rates, time-to-resolution, and NPS via in-app analytics, reinforcing continuous improvement. These flows are designed with an API-first approach to integrate seamlessly into existing enterprise systems, aligning with industry best practices in product management and agility.	\N	\N	{"primary_agent": "strategy", "coordination_mode": "enhanced_collaborative", "agent_interactions": []}	2025-11-30 01:05:24.542659+00	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
7a67221d-5920-49f2-83fc-73261cfc8600	a7b8c9d0-e1f2-4345-a678-901234567890	a7b8c9d0-e1f2-4345-a678-901234567890	322aaeb6-155b-448c-a211-d6c4b68e598a	agent	Design Phase	design	## Design Phase Content\n\n### V0 Vercel Prompt\nModel: v0-1.5-md  \nProject goal\n- Provide a cohesive, persona-driven platform for product managers, IT/ops leads, and customer support managers to unify fragmented workflows (onboarding, task management, collaboration, feedback/analytics).\n- Deliver a mobile-first, card-based dashboard, onboarding flows, task management UI, side-panel collaboration/chat, document sharing, and analytics pages.\n- Prioritize accessibility (WCAG AA), keyboard navigation, and an API-first integration approach.\n\nDeliverables\n- Clear folder structure and a README with start instructions.\n- Unit test examples (Jest + React Testing Library) for 2â€“3 core components.\n- Accessibility notes & checklist in README.\n- Storybook entries or at least component examples in a Playground page.\n\n  - primary: slate-800 / text & UI grounding â€” use bg-slate-800 / text-white for hero contrast (#1F2937).\n  - success: emerald-500 (#10B981)\n  - danger/error: rose-500 (#F43F5E)\n  - surface: slate-50 / slate-100 for cards and backgrounds\n  - muted text: slate-500 / slate-600 for secondary copy\n- Typography:\n  - font-family: Inter (preferred) with fallback Roboto / system fonts\n  - Headings: font-semibold, scale: H1 28-32px, H2 20-24px, H3 16-18px\n  - Body: 16px / text-base, leading-6\n- Border radius: rounded-md for controls, rounded-xl for bigger containers.\n- Shadows: subtle: shadow-sm for cards, shadow-md for elevated modals.\n\nAccessibility & interaction states\n- All interactive elements must include ARIA labels, role attributes where applicable, and keyboard-accessible behavior.\n- Ensure WCAG AA contrast ratios for text and interactive elements (provide alternate token set if necessary).\n- Focus styles: ring-2 ring-offset-2 ring-sky-400 for focus-visible. Use :focus-visible not just :focus.\n- Modals and side panels must implement focus-trap and restore focus on close.\n- Provide skip-to-content link at top of each page.\n- Use semantic HTML (nav, main, header, footer, form, button).\n- Provide keyboard shortcuts/ARIA for chat input (e.g., Shift+Enter new line, Enter send) and visible hints.\n\nMobile-first & responsive breakpoints\n- Mobile-first layout: design for 375â€“420px width initially, then sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px).\n- Collapsible navigation: bottom or top bar on mobile; persistent left sidebar on md+ screens.\n- Card-based grid: single column on mobile, 2-3 columns on md/lg using CSS grid (e.g., grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4).\n- Task list: collapse to compact list on small screens; keep table view on md+ with sticky headers.\n\nUI components to generate (detailed)\n1) Global layout & navigation\n- Top-level Layout component (AppLayout) with:\n  - header: left: logo + product name (provide SVG), center: global search (optional), right: user menu (avatar, role switcher).\n  - mobile navigation: responsive hamburger -> slide-over menu.\n  - left navigation (md+): vertical nav with icons/labels (Home/Dashboard, Tasks, Collaboration, Analytics, Integrations, Settings).\n  - skip-to-content skip link.\n- Provide route structure suggestions:\n/ (Landing) /onboarding /dashboard /tasks /tasks/[id] /collaboration /analytics /settings\n\n2) Landing / Marketing page (Hero)\n- Hero with value prop, 2 CTAs (Primary: "Get started", Secondary: "Request demo").\n- Features block with 3â€“4 feature cards (icons + title + short desc).\n- Testimonials slider (use accessible carousel with aria-live region).\n- Footer with links & copyright.\n\n3) Onboarding flow (multi-step)\n- Signup/login form (email + password + SSO button placeholders).\n- Stepper component (progress bar + step labels).\n- Guided tutorial modal/overlay with progressive disclosure (Next, Prev, Exit), keyboard accessible.\n- Personalization page: toggles for notifications, dropdowns for default workspace, role selection (Product Manager, IT/Ops, Support), initial integrations checklist.\n- Provide sample localStorage persistence for onboarding state.\n\n4) Dashboard (card-based)\n- Mobile-first card grid with:\n  - Prioritized Tasks card (top N tasks), quick actions (Create, Filter, Sort).\n  - Activity/Collaboration feed (recent comments, mentions).\n  - Shortcuts card (Create task, Upload doc, New incident).\n  - SLA/metrics snapshot (task completion %, avg time-to-resolve).\n- Each card must be accessible, tiltable hover effect (framer-motion small lift), and have keyboard focusability.\n\n5) Task management\n- Task List (md+ table view with sortable columns; mobile list view with accordion-like expand).\n  - Columns: Checkbox (bulk), Title, Assignee avatar, Due date, Priority (chip), Status (chip), Actions (edit, more).\n  - Sorting + filtering UI (dropdowns) with accessible labels.\n- Task creation modal (or right-side panel):\n  - Fields: Title, Description (rich-text or plain with markdown preview toggle), Assignee (typeahead), Due date (date picker), Priority, Attachments (drag-and-drop), Tags, Link to related docs/tasks.\n  - Comments section inside task detail with threaded comments, emoji reactions, and attachments.\n  - Action row: Save Draft, Save & Notify, Mark as Complete.\n- Task detail route: /tasks/[id] shows full details; include activity log & history.\n- Data model (TypeScript interfaces):\n  interface User { id: string; name: string; email: string; avatarUrl?: string; role: 'pm'|'ops'|'support'; }\n  interface Attachment { id: string; fileName: string; url: string; mimeType: string; size: number; }\n  interface Comment { id: string; authorId: string; content: string; createdAt: string; attachments?: Attachment[]; }\n  interface Task { id: string; title: string; description?: string; assigneeId?: string; status: 'todo'|'in_progress'|'blocked'|'done'; priority: 'low'|'medium'|'high'; dueDate?: string; tags?: string[]; attachments?: Attachment[]; comments?: Comment[]; createdAt: string; updatedAt?: string; }\n\n6) Collaboration & Chat side-panel\n- Right-side collapsible panel or persistent on wide screens.\n- Chat list (channels & direct messages) with unread counts, keyboard navigation, and search.\n- Chat message list must support file previews (images, PDFs), link previews, and mention highlighting.\n- Chat input with accessible ARIA and keyboard behaviors; show typing indicator and message status.\n- Option to convert a chat message into a task (quick action).\n\n7) Document sharing & uploads\n- Drag-and-drop zone that shows progress bars for uploads, previews for images and PDFs.\n- Document library with thumbnails, search, file meta (owner, uploaded date, linked tasks).\n- Ability to link/upload files directly from Task creation view.\n\n8) Analytics & Feedback dashboard\n- Card-based analytics with charts (use simple chart placeholders with accessible alt text; recommend Recharts or Chart.js).\n- KPIs: task completion rate, avg time-to-resolution, open vs closed tasks, NPS summary.\n- Filters by team/role/time range.\n- Export CSV button and shareable snapshot link (copy to clipboard).\n\n9) Integrations page\n- Integrations marketplace card list (ServiceNow, Salesforce, Atlassian, Slack). Each integration has install CTA, and configuration modal with OAuth or API-key placeholder flows.\n\n10) Settings & Admin\n- Workspace settings, user management (invite, role assignment), audit logs.\nState management & API-first approach\n- Use React Query or SWR for remote data fetching patterns; include sample fetch hooks (useTasks, useUsers, useAnalytics).\n- Create mock API endpoints under /pages/api (or app/api) to serve sample JSON for tasks, users, analytics.\n- Provide a mock integration service layer that returns Promise<...> so real API wiring is straightforward.\n\nAnimations & transitions\n  - Card hover lift (y -2px, scale 1.01)\n  - Modal slide-in (from bottom) and overlay fade\n  - Collapse/expand transitions for mobile lists\n- Motion must be reduced when prefers-reduced-motion is set.\n\nTesting & quality\n- Provide unit tests for:\n  - TaskCard component (rendering, click handlers).\n  - TaskModal (open/close focus trap).\n  - Nav accessibility (skip link works).\n- Provide linting and formatting config (ESLint + Prettier) and tsconfig.\n\nDeveloper instructions & README\n- Clear steps to run locally (install, dev, build, start).\n- How to replace mock APIs with real backends (endpoints to swap).\n- Accessibility checklist describing ARIA patterns used, keyboard interactions, and manual audit steps.\n\nExtra requirements / Output expectations for V0\n- Provide file-by-file output for the main pieces (or a zipped repository) including:\n  - app/layout.tsx and app/page.tsx (dashboard)\n  - components/* (AppLayout, TopNav, SideNav, Card, TaskList, TaskCard, TaskModal, ChatPanel, UploadDropzone, AnalyticsCard)\n  - lib/hooks.ts (useTasks, useUsers)\n  - data/sample/*.json (tasks, users, comments, analytics)\n  - pages/api/* mock endpoints\n  - README.md and ACCESSIBILITY.md\n- Provide a short visual spec for each major page/component (desktop & mobile screenshots mock annotations or descriptions).\nTone & design brief to the generator\n- Clean, modern, enterprise-friendly aesthetic: minimal, calm palette with Sky Blue CTAs and Slate grounding.\n- Emphasize clarity, speed-to-value, and low cognitive load for power users.\n- Components must be reusable, documented, and easily integrated into an enterprise environment.\n\nSample prompt summary to include at top of request to V0\nOptional (if you want additional scope)\n- Add SSO simulation (Okta/Google) placeholder and onboarding analytics tracking (page events).\n- Provide a dark mode design variant.\n\nPaste the full content above into V0. If you want, I can also:\n- Call the V0 Platform API to create the project using this prompt (I can submit it for you).\n- Or generate a more compact prompt for faster iteration (smaller scope: dashboard + tasks only).\n\nWhich would you like next?\n\n**Score: 4/5**\n\n**Design Phase Score: 4/5**\n\n	## Design Phase Content\n\n### V0 Vercel Prompt\nModel: v0-1.5-md  \nProject goal\n- Provide a cohesive, persona-driven platform for product managers, IT/ops leads, and customer support managers to unify fragmented workflows (onboarding, task management, collaboration, feedback/analytics).\n- Deliver a mobile-first, card-based dashboard, onboarding flows, task management UI, side-panel collaboration/chat, document sharing, and analytics pages.\n- Prioritize accessibility (WCAG AA), keyboard navigation, and an API-first integration approach.\n\nDeliverables\n- Clear folder structure and a README with start instructions.\n- Unit test examples (Jest + React Testing Library) for 2â€“3 core components.\n- Accessibility notes & checklist in README.\n- Storybook entries or at least component examples in a Playground page.\n\n  - primary: slate-800 / text & UI grounding â€” use bg-slate-800 / text-white for hero contrast (#1F2937).\n  - success: emerald-500 (#10B981)\n  - danger/error: rose-500 (#F43F5E)\n  - surface: slate-50 / slate-100 for cards and backgrounds\n  - muted text: slate-500 / slate-600 for secondary copy\n- Typography:\n  - font-family: Inter (preferred) with fallback Roboto / system fonts\n  - Headings: font-semibold, scale: H1 28-32px, H2 20-24px, H3 16-18px\n  - Body: 16px / text-base, leading-6\n- Border radius: rounded-md for controls, rounded-xl for bigger containers.\n- Shadows: subtle: shadow-sm for cards, shadow-md for elevated modals.\n\nAccessibility & interaction states\n- All interactive elements must include ARIA labels, role attributes where applicable, and keyboard-accessible behavior.\n- Ensure WCAG AA contrast ratios for text and interactive elements (provide alternate token set if necessary).\n- Focus styles: ring-2 ring-offset-2 