ons page\n- Integrations marketplace card list (ServiceNow, Salesforce, Atlassian, Slack). Each integration has install CTA, and configuration modal with OAuth or API-key placeholder flows.\n\n10) Settings & Admin\n- Workspace settings, user management (invite, role assignment), audit logs.\nState management & API-first approach\n- Use React Query or SWR for remote data fetching patterns; include sample fetch hooks (useTasks, useUsers, useAnalytics).\n- Create mock API endpoints under /pages/api (or app/api) to serve sample JSON for tasks, users, analytics.\n- Provide a mock integration service layer that returns Promise<...> so real API wiring is straightforward.\n\nAnimations & transitions\n  - Card hover lift (y -2px, scale 1.01)\n  - Modal slide-in (from bottom) and overlay fade\n  - Collapse/expand transitions for mobile lists\n- Motion must be reduced when prefers-reduced-motion is set.\n\nTesting & quality\n- Provide unit tests for:\n  - TaskCard component (rendering, click handlers).\n  - TaskModal (open/close focus trap).\n  - Nav accessibility (skip link works).\n- Provide linting and formatting config (ESLint + Prettier) and tsconfig.\n\nDeveloper instructions & README\n- Clear steps to run locally (install, dev, build, start).\n- How to replace mock APIs with real backends (endpoints to swap).\n- Accessibility checklist describing ARIA patterns used, keyboard interactions, and manual audit steps.\n\nExtra requirements / Output expectations for V0\n- Provide file-by-file output for the main pieces (or a zipped repository) including:\n  - app/layout.tsx and app/page.tsx (dashboard)\n  - components/* (AppLayout, TopNav, SideNav, Card, TaskList, TaskCard, TaskModal, ChatPanel, UploadDropzone, AnalyticsCard)\n  - lib/hooks.ts (useTasks, useUsers)\n  - data/sample/*.json (tasks, users, comments, analytics)\n  - pages/api/* mock endpoints\n  - README.md and ACCESSIBILITY.md\n- Provide a short visual spec for each major page/component (desktop & mobile screensho